Manchester Metropolitan University Overview

Manchester Metropolitan University is a public university located in Manchester, England. The university traces its origins to the Manchester Mechanics Institute and the Manchester School of Design, which formed Manchester Polytechnic in 1970. Manchester Polytechnic then gained university status under the government's Further and Higher Education Act, becoming the Manchester Metropolitan University in 1992. Today, it is headquartered in the city of Manchester. Here to make an impact on Manchester, our nation and beyond, with a driving ambition to discover and disseminate knowledge, and make higher education accessible and beneficial to all those with the passion and ability to succeed.

Manchester Metropolitan University Admission Requirement

The following requirements must be fulfilled to get admitted to the Manchester Metropolitan University.

  • International students are considered on case-by-case basis. There can be some additional requirements, depending on the program you are applying to.
  • Students are required to submit their original transcripts from their last attended academic institutions. If they are not in English, then submit the translated copies of the same along with the originals.
  • Applicants must be 18 years old at the time of the beginning of the course.
  • You need to submit your English language proficiency test scores if you are coming from a non-English speaking country.

Manchester Metropolitan University Students

  • Food & Dining Services
  • IT Services
  • Library Services
  • Social & Cultural Events
  • Students Club & Socities
  • Student Wellbeing
  • Student Hub

  • Students’ Union Advice Centre
  • The MMU Writing Project
  • The Skills Online
  • Student Support Officers

Manchester Metropolitan University Scholarships

International scholarships and funding

Find out how you can get help with the cost of studying at Manchester Metropolitan.

If you want to study at university in the UK, a scholarship can be a big help.

Scholarships for international students in the UK come from two main sources, from:

  • The university they will attend
  • Other international organisations

Find a scholarship at Manchester Metropolitan

We offer four different types of scholarship for international students:

  • General and Chancellor’s international awards
  • Postgraduate scholarships for specific courses
  • Research grants
  • Sports scholarships
